1	// Increment 4 — Teams transcript ingestion.
2	//
3	// Triggered by the webhook (apps/web/app/api/teams/notifications) when Graph
4	// pushes a transcript notification. Fetches the WebVTT, turns each speaker turn
5	// into a `messages` row inside a channel that represents the call, and leaves
6	// them as extraction_status='pending' so the existing claim-extraction cron
7	// picks them up — NOTHING here writes to claims directly (candidate-before-claim).
8	//
9	// Design notes:
10	//   - Each utterance = one message with role='user', employeeId = the resolved
11	//     speaker (or null when we can't match the name). This preserves speaker
12	//     attribution + verbatim quotes for evidence, exactly like chat messages.
13	//   - Idempotent: re-running for the same transcript is a no-op (clientMessageId
14	//     `teams:<transcriptId>:<n>` is the dedupe key).
15	//
16	// Known v1 limitations (intentional, documented for follow-up):
17	//   - Speaker→employee match is by display-name (case-insensitive) against
18	//     employees.name. Teams VTT carries display names, not emails/AAD ids, so
19	//     unmatched speakers get a null employeeId. TODO: resolve via AAD id when
20	//     the decrypted resource exposes participant identities.
21	//   - Message createdAt is anchored to ingestion time + the cue offset (so all
22	//     cues cluster into a single extraction segment). TODO: anchor to the real
23	//     meeting start when available.
