68	/**
69	 * Approve a proposal. The mutation depends on the proposal type:
70	 *
71	 *   - create_top_domain → INSERT into knowledge_top_domains using the
72	 *     proposal payload (boundary rules included). This is the only
73	 *     mutation currently implemented inline; the reclassification path
74	 *     for merge_top_domains / split_top_domain / reassign_claims /
75	 *     create_sub_topic / merge_sub_topics / split_sub_topic / retire_sub_topic
76	 *     is scaffolded as a TODO — those need targeted reclassification of
77	 *     claim_top_domains / claim_sub_topics rows + optional Brain
78	 *     synthesis re-runs (the "transactional reclassification job"
79	 *     from R10.5 task 4 in the retrofit packet).
80	 *
81	 *   For the unimplemented branches, the proposal is marked approved
82	 *   (recording the reviewer) and the change log row is written, but
83	 *   the actual reclassification is queued as a TODO note. This
84	 *   preserves the audit trail without auto-mutating the taxonomy
